SIMPLE: percher
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Percher
<hw>Perch"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Perch</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which,
perches.</def> <rj><au>J. Burroughs.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the Insessores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[From <er>Perch</er> a pole.]</ety> <def>A Paris
candle anciently used in England; also, a large wax candle formerly set
upon the altar.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Percheron</ent>⟦br⟧
